<subSubSection id="04F2655027431208A90336C2FB22FE13" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27431208A90336C2FB22FE13" blockId="10.[848,1491,410,497]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927431208A90336C2FC6BFE50" bold="true" box="[848,987,410,434]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927431208A90336C2FC0EFE50" bold="true" box="[848,958,410,434]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
First flagellomere 1.2 times as long as wide. Fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brownish. Dorsal lobe of surstyli with plumose hair.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F2655027431209A9033542FD82FC07" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27431208A9033542FC69FDB3" blockId="10.[848,1491,538,593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927431208A9033542FB9CFDD0" bold="true" box="[848,1068,538,562]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927431208A9033542FC7FFDD0" bold="true" box="[848,975,538,562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
. – Male
</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E27431208AE973542FAF8FDD3" box="[1220,1352,538,561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.7 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E27431208A9033562FC65FDB3" box="[848,981,570,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27431208A9033522FB20FC93" blockId="10.[848,1491,634,881]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Head metallic green with pale grey pollen. Face narrowing downward, narrower than first flagellomere. Hairs and bristles black. Postocular bristles (including posteroventral hairs) black. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E27431208A9AD3582FBFCFD13" box="[1022,1100,730,753]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[137,1505,943,2087]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 29–32. Hercostomus plumatus, new species, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) brownish; first flagellomere darker, 1.2 times as long as wide; arista dark brown, minutely pubescent with short basal segment. Proboscis brownish yellow with black hairs, palpus brownish yellow with black hairs and black apical bristle.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1897665327431208AAC73F63FB52F7B2" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5339243" box="[148,1250,2107,2128]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" startId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" targetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27431208AAC73F63FB52F7B2" blockId="10.[148,1250,2107,2128]" box="[148,1250,2107,2128]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 29–32. 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D5827431208AB463F63FE43F7B2" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[277,499,2107,2128]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumatus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927431208AB463F63FE43F7B2" box="[277,499,2107,2128]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Hercostomus plumatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B227431208A8523F63FDC9F7B2" box="[513,633,2107,2128]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D3796FEECFD27" blockId="11.[126,765,206,709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Thorax metallic green with pale grey pollen. Six strong dc, 5–6 pairs of acr; scutellum with two pairs of bristles (basal pair short and weak). Propleuron with 1 black bristle on lower part. Legs yellow; fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brownish. Mid and hind tarsi from tip of tarsomere 1 onward brownish to brown. Hairs and bristles black. Mid and hind coxae each with 1 exterior bristle. Mid and hind femora each with 1 preapical bristle. Fore tibia with 2 ad and 1 weak pd, apically with 3 bristles; mid tibia with 3 ad, 2 pd and 1 av, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 4 ad, 3 pd and 2 vs., apically with 3 bristles. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres LI 1.0: 0.5: 0.2: 0.15: 0.15: 0.15; LII 1.5: 0.65: 0.4: 0.3: 0.2: 0.2; LIII 1.65: 0.5: 0.7: 0.5: 0.35: 0.25. Wing hyaline, tinged with greyish, veins brown; CuAx ratio 0.9, R4+5 and M parallel apically. Squama yellow with black hairs. Halter yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D35B6FD3BFC67" blockId="11.[126,765,750,901]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
Abdomen metallic green with pale grey pollen. Hairs and bristles black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E27421209ABE13456FD82FCC7" box="[434,562,782,805]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[137,1505,943,2087]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 29–32. Hercostomus plumatus, new species, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Figs. 30–32</figureCitation>
): Epandrium longer than wide, lateral epandrial lobe slightly curved apically with 3 bristles; cercus nearly triangular; hypandrium narrow and straight; aedeagus with 1 minute, inner denticle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D34F5FD82FC07" blockId="11.[126,765,941,997]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D34F5FF68FC27" bold="true" box="[126,216,941,965]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E27421209AB3A34F6FE0DFC27" box="[361,445,942,965]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="8B109B3E27421209A81C34F6FD14FC27" box="[591,676,942,965]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but fore tibia without weak pd.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F2655027421209AA2D3355FE70FBA7" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D3355FE70FBA7" blockId="11.[126,764,1037,1093]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D3355FEBFFBC7" bold="true" box="[126,271,1037,1061]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D3355FF43FBC7" bold="true" box="[126,243,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Etymology</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the plumose hair on the dorsal lobe of surstyli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F2655027421209AA2D3335FE2CFB67" box="[126,412,1133,1157]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D3335FE2CFB67" blockId="11.[126,412,1133,1157]" box="[126,412,1133,1157]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D3335FEAFFB67" bold="true" box="[126,287,1133,1157]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D3335FEB3FB67" bold="true" box="[126,259,1133,1157]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Distribution</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="34FF764B27421209AB7B3336FE28FB67" box="[296,408,1134,1157]" name="Singapore" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Singapore</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F2655027421209AA2D33F5FD4EFAA7" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB27421209AA2D33F5FD4EFAA7" blockId="11.[126,766,1197,1349]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D33F5FEB1FB27" bold="true" box="[126,257,1197,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AA2D33F5FF52FB27" bold="true" box="[126,226,1197,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D5827421209A8B133F6FF46FB07" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209A8B133F6FF46FB07" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">H. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B227421209AB523396FE31FB07" box="[257,385,1230,1253]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but may be separated from the latter by its triangular cercus and aedeagus with 1 inner denticle; in 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D5827421209AACA3256FE82FAC7" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[153,306,1294,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC927421209AACA3256FE82FAC7" box="[153,306,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">H. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B227421209AB133256FE73FAC7" box="[320,451,1294,1317]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the cercus is strongly curved and nearly geniculate and the aedeagus has 2 inner denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
